<subSubSection pageId="1" pageNumber="554" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="1.[151,1437,331,754]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,308,475,501]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Remarks</emphasis>
. The fishtail-shaped sclerotized dorsobasal marking on aedeagal tube, a long ventrally directed spine about as long as one fourth aedeagal length and the slender, nail-shaped median sclerite with an enlarged tip of the above specimens, indicate that these males are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName authority="Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010" authorityName="Sivec &amp; Stark" authorityYear="2010" box="[949,1436,547,573]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="gorohovi">
<emphasis box="[949,1187,547,573]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Chinoperla gorohovi</emphasis>
<bibRefCitation author="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P." box="[1198,1436,547,573]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" pagination="62 - 74" refId="ref2190" refString="Sivec, I. &amp; Stark, B. P. (2010) Five new species of Chinoperla Zwick (Plecoptera: Perlidae) from Vietnam and Thailand. Illiesia, 6 (8), 62 - 74." type="journal article" year="2010">Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010</bibRefCitation>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[159,229,583,609]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[151,250,1494,1518]" captionTargetBox="[167,1420,181,1454]" captionTargetId="figure-19@3.[167,1421,181,1469]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Chinoperla gorohovi Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010 (male)A.Aedeagus, dorsal view.B.Aedeagus, ventral view. C.Aedeagus, lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). Although much paler distally, the forewing subcosta (Sc) of these fully aged specimens seems normal in length (
<figureCitation box="[238,325,619,645]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,788,1707]" captionTargetId="figure-211@1.[157,1430,777,1717]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chinoperla gorohovi Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010 (male). A. Adult habitus, dorsal view. B. Forewing." pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Fig. 1B</figureCitation>
), which previously is only known in 
<taxonomicName authority="(Wu, 1948) (Mo et al. 2021)" authorityName="Mo et al." authorityYear="2021" baseAuthorityName="Wu" baseAuthorityYear="1948" box="[750,1256,619,646]" class="Insecta" family="Perlidae" genus="Chinoperla" kingdom="Animalia" order="Plecoptera" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="nigroflavata">
<emphasis box="[750,921,619,646]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">C. nigroflavata</emphasis>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wu, C. F." box="[937,1050,619,645]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" pagination="75 - 80" refId="ref2278" refString="Wu, C. F. (1948) Fourth supplement to the stoneflies of China (Order Plecoptera). Peking Natural History Bulletin, 17 (1), 75 - 80." type="journal article" year="1948">Wu, 1948</bibRefCitation>
) (
<bibRefCitation author="Mo, R. R. &amp; Liu, R. J. &amp; Wang, G. Q. &amp; Li, W. H. &amp; Muranyi, D." box="[1074,1248,619,646]" pageId="1" pageNumber="554" pagination="62 - 85" refId="ref2074" refString="Mo, R. R., Liu, R. J., Wang, G. Q., Li, W. H. &amp; Muranyi, D. (2021) Review of the genus Chinoperla Zwick, 1980 (Plecoptera: Perlidae: Perlinae) from China. European Journal of Taxonomy, 775, 62 - 85. https: // doi. org / 10.5852 / ejt. 2021.775.1547" type="journal article" year="2021">
Mo 
<emphasis box="[1123,1173,619,645]" italics="true" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">et al</emphasis>
. 2021
</bibRefCitation>
)
</taxonomicName>
. The specimens from 
<collectingRegion box="[215,455,655,681]" country="China" name="Guangdong" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Guangdong Province</collectingRegion>
have short Sc possibly because of paler subcostal area due to long preservation. The darker habitus (
<figureCitation box="[329,430,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="1.[151,250,1741,1765]" captionTargetBox="[170,1416,788,1707]" captionTargetId="figure-211@1.[157,1430,777,1717]" captionTargetPageId="1" captionText="FIGURE 1. Chinoperla gorohovi Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010 (male). A. Adult habitus, dorsal view. B. Forewing." pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Figs. 1A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[443,479,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[201,1419,181,1513]" captionTargetId="figure-31@2.[158,1430,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chinoperla gorohovi Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010 (male). A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia before NaOH treatment, dorsal view. C. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. D. Cleared terminalia, oblique lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="554">2A</figureCitation>
) and the obtuse tip of hemitergal processes (
<figureCitation box="[990,1125,691,717]" captionStart="FIGURE 2" captionStartId="2.[151,250,1546,1570]" captionTargetBox="[201,1419,181,1513]" captionTargetId="figure-31@2.[158,1430,181,1522]" captionTargetPageId="2" captionText="FIGURE 2. Chinoperla gorohovi Sivec &amp; Stark, 2010 (male). A. Head and pronotum, dorsal view. B. Terminalia before NaOH treatment, dorsal view. C. Cleared terminalia, dorsal view. D. Cleared terminalia, oblique lateral view." pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Figs. 2B–D</figureCitation>
), herein can be regarded as intraspecific variation. The species is recorded in 
<collectingRegion box="[706,899,727,754]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="1" pageNumber="554">Yunnan Province</collectingRegion>
for the first time.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
